"answer": "Under Section 141, if a person is ordered to give security for keeping the peace, the Magistrate shall make an order accordingly. The powers include specifying the amount and duration of security, ensuring it is not excessive, and directing the execution of a bond with or without sureties. For minors, the bond must be executed only by their sureties.",
